fields.description:
*Assessment*

euca-delete-bundle does not work for 4.0.0.  The following can be seen:

{code}
# # euca-bundle-and-upload-image -i trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader -r x86_64 --kernel true -b trusty-server-paravirt-20140409
/var/tmp/bundle-vG2oNo/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader.part.00 100% |=====================================================================================================|  89.38 kB  42.27 kB/s Time: 0:00:02
/var/tmp/bundle-vG2oNo/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader.manifest.xml 100% |================================================================================================|   3.39 kB   1.56 kB/s Time: 0:00:02
Uploaded trusty-server-paravirt-20140409/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader.manifest.xml
# euca-delete-bundle -b trusty-server-paravirt-20140409 -p trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader
euca-delete-bundle: error: download_files() takes exactly 2 non-keyword arguments (3 given)
{code}

*Signs*

* euca-delete-bundle with debug output:
{code}
# euca-delete-bundle -b trusty-server-paravirt-20140409 -p trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader --debug

2014-04-09 08:45:49,549 DEBUG   S3RestAuth b64-encoded signature: d8N/nrS4fXki4P0DrtZIapjnwss=

2014-04-09 08:45:49,558 DEBUG   Walrus request param:  max-keys: 0

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/bin/euca-delete-bundle", line 6, in <module>
    euca2ools.commands.bundle.deletebundle.DeleteBundle.run()
  File "/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/requestbuilder/command.py", line 286, in run

{code}
* Help message from euca-delete-bundle:
{code}
# euca-delete-bundle --help
usage: euca-delete-bundle -b BUCKET[/PREFIX] (-m MANIFEST | -p PREFIX)
                          [--clear] [-U URL] [--region USER@REGION]
                          [-I KEY_ID] [-S KEY] [--security-token TOKEN]
                          [--debug] [--debugger] [--version] [-h]

Delete a previously-uploaded bundle

optional arguments:
  -b BUCKET[/PREFIX], --bucket BUCKET[/PREFIX]
                        location of the bundle to delete (required)
  -m MANIFEST, --manifest MANIFEST
                        use a local manifest file to figure out what to delete
  -p PREFIX, --prefix PREFIX
                        delete the bundle that begins with a specific prefix
                        (e.g. "fry" for "fry.manifest.xml")
  --clear               attempt to delete the bucket as well
  -U URL, --url URL     storage service endpoint URL
  --region USER@REGION  region and/or user names to search when looking up
                        config file data
  -I KEY_ID, --access-key-id KEY_ID
  -S KEY, --secret-key KEY
  --security-token TOKEN
  --debug               show debugging output
  --debugger            launch interactive debugger on error
  --version             show the program's version and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
{code}
* Version of euca2ools:
{code}
# euca-version
euca2ools 3.1.0-pre1-27-g697a082 (Omega)
eucalyptus 4.0.0
{code}

*Pertinent Data*

This works in 3.4.2, so I am thinking this should be a regression.

*Steps*

* Set up a Eucalyptus 4.0 Cloud
* Use euca-bundle-and-upload-image to bundle and upload an image. For example,
{code}
# euca-bundle-and-upload-image -i trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader -r x86_64 --kernel true -b trusty-server-paravirt-20140409
{code}
* Attempt to delete the bundle, and observe the behavior:
{code}
# euca-delete-bundle -b trusty-server-paravirt-20140409 -p trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-loader --clear
euca-delete-bundle: error: download_files() takes exactly 2 non-keyword arguments (3 given)
{code}
